        "title": "fix(minimax): guard music generation SSE JSON.parse against malformed frames",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.ts:266` calls `JSON.parse(json)` on SSE data frames without try/catch. A malformed SSE data frame → unhandled `SyntaxError` → music generation crashes instead of skipping the bad frame.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.ts`: wrap `JSON.parse(json)` in try/catch → `continue` (skip frame) on malformed SSE data\n- `extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.test.ts`: test verifying malformed SSE frames are skipped and valid audio frames still processed\n\nLabel: bugfix | merge-risk: 🟢 minimal | AI-assisted\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Unit test — exercises actual code path via mocked SSE stream\n\nThe test sends mixed `data: NOT JSON {{{` + valid audio frame through the provider and verifies:\n- Malformed frame is gracefully skipped (no crash)\n- Valid audio frame is decoded into `result.tracks[0].buffer`\n\n```\n$ pnpm exec vitest run extensions/minimax/music-generation-provider.test.ts\n\n ✓ skips malformed SSE data frames and processes valid audio frames\n ... (all existing tests pass)\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n```\n\n### Patch logic\n\n`readStreamingTrack` processes SSE `data:` lines from the MiniMax music generation stream. Before this fix, `JSON.parse(json)` on a malformed frame would throw `SyntaxError` and crash the generation. After the fix, malformed frames hit `continue` (skip), matching the same defensive pattern used for `[DONE]` and empty lines.",
